# Mandatory Testing For Feature Changes

- For any new feature, UI addition, or behavioral change, add or update test cases that cover:
  - Happy path behavior
  - Relevant edge/error states
  - Regression risk for touched flows
- Run all newly added or updated tests and confirm they pass before completing work.
- If the change affects dependent features/modules, run tests for those dependent areas too.
- Do not mark work complete until required tests are implemented and verified as passing.
- If test execution is blocked (environment/tooling), clearly report what was attempted, what failed, and exact commands needed to verify.
